How to collect ODF must-gather data
https://access.redhat.com/solutions/7068449

Data Collection for Red Hat OpenShift Data Foundation(ODF)
For ODF-4.13 and above (Rebase to RHEL9)

Examples:

$ oc adm must-gather --image=registry.redhat.io/odf4/odf-must-gather-rhel9:v4.13 --dest-dir=odf-<ddMM>

example 1:

$ oc adm must-gather --image=registry.redhat.io/odf4/odf-must-gather-rhel9:v4.13 --dest-dir=odf-1Jun

example 2:

$ oc adm must-gather --image=$(oc -n openshift-storage get deployment.apps/ocs-operator -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.metadata.annotations.operators\.openshift\.io/must-gather-image}') --dest-dir=.

if the MG fails due to a timeout, increase the timeout, example:

$ oc adm must-gather --image=registry.redhat.io/odf4/odf-must-gather-rhel9:v4.13 --dest-dir=odf-1Jun --request-timeout=2m 

If the must-gather is unable to complete or takes too long, please run the below commands on your bastion or follow [3]:

$ oc get nodes
$ oc get co
$ oc get clusterversion
$ oc get backingstore -n openshift-storage
$ oc get storagecluster -n openshift-storage -o yaml
$ oc get csv -n openshift-storage
$ oc get olm -n openshift-storage
$ oc get pod -o wide -n openshift-storage
$ oc get pvc -n openshift-storage
$ oc get pv
$ oc get sc
$ oc get jobs -n openshift-storage
$ oc get events --sort-by='.lastTimestamp' -n openshift-storage

